===============

### Description of the project
--------------------------

This Ој-project consists in building a simple compiler for arithmetic expressions.

We work with two small languages:

- Expr: a high-level language with arithmetic expressions
- Pfx: a stack-based language executed by a virtual machine

The goal is to understand how an expression can be:

1. parsed into an abstract syntax tree (AST)
2. evaluated directly
3. translated into a lower-level language (Pfx)

Up to exercise 6, we focused on parsing and evaluating expressions.


===============

### Sources
-------

Git repository: https://github.com/paulamalvarador-commits/compilation

===============

### How toвҖҰ
-------

вҖҰretrieve the sources?

  git clone https://github.com/paulamalvarador-commits/compilation

вҖҰcompile?

  dune build

вҖҰexecute and test?

To evaluate an expression:

  dune exec expr/main.exe expr/basic/tests/an_example.expr

===============

### Running tests
-------------

We created a small test suite to validate the behavior of our Pfx virtual machine.  
Each test is stored in a separate `.pfx` file located in:

pfx/basic/tests/

### Running a single test

To execute one test file, use:

  dune exec ./pfx/pfxVM.exe -- pfx/basic/tests/<test_file>.pfx

Example:

  dune exec ./pfx/pfxVM.exe -- pfx/basic/tests/t2_add.pfx


### Running all tests automatically

We provide a script `run_tests.sh` at the root of the project to execute multiple tests:

  ./run_tests.sh

This script runs several predefined test cases and displays their outputs.

### Test coverage

The test suite covers:

- Basic stack operations (`push`, `pop`, `swap`)
- Arithmetic operations (`add`, `sub`, `mul`, `div`, `rem`)
- Stack errors (empty stack, insufficient elements)
- Arithmetic errors (division by zero)
- Argument handling (correct and incorrect number of arguments)
- Comments and formatting in input files

===============


===============

Structure of the project
------------------------

- expr/: handles expressions (parsing and evaluation)
  - basic/
    - ast.ml: defines the structure of expressions (Const, Binop, etc.)
    - eval.ml: evaluates expressions
    - lexer.mll: converts text into tokens
    - parser.mly: builds the AST from tokens
    - toPfx.ml: (to be completed later) translates Expr to Pfx
  - common/
    - binOp.ml: defines arithmetic operations (+, -, *, /, %)
  - main.ml: runs the expression evaluator
  - compiler.ml: will be used for translation to Pfx

- pfx/: implements a stack-based virtual machine
  - basic/
    - ast.ml: defines Pfx instructions (Push, Add, etc.)
    - eval.ml: executes Pfx programs
    - lexer.mll / parser.mly: parse Pfx programs
  - pfxVM.ml: main file for executing Pfx programs

- utils/: helper modules (e.g., file location handling)


